The Vietnam War ends, as North Vietnamese forces take Saigon.  April 30, 1980 - Queen Juliana of the Netherlands abdicates the throne, and her daughter becomes Queen Beatrix of the Netherlands.
Beatrix later also abdicates, on this day in 2013, in favor of her son, King Willem-Alexander of the Netherlands.
It is the world's fifth largest country.
The country has about 201 million people.
In the late 1500s and early 1600s the Dutch and the French would sometimes try to take land in Brazil.
In 1889, Brazil became a republic.
Other people in Brazil speak indigenous Brazilian languages, Italian, Japanese, French, or Spanish.
It is known for its many rainforests and jungles.
